{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":884,"text":"When we use the word \"architect\" or \"designer,\""},{"time":4053,"text":"what we usually mean is a professional,"},{"time":6852,"text":"someone who gets paid,"},{"time":9324,"text":"and we tend to assume that it's those professionals"},{"time":12247,"text":"who are going to be the ones to help us solve"},{"time":14228,"text":"the really big, systemic design challenges that we face"},{"time":16788,"text":"like climate change, urbanization and social inequality."},{"time":20633,"text":"That's our kind of working presumption."},{"time":23717,"text":"And I think it's wrong, actually."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26724,"text":"In 2008, I was just about to graduate from architecture school"},{"time":29972,"text":"after several years, and go out and get a job,"},{"time":32645,"text":"and this happened."},{"time":35570,"text":"The economy ran out of jobs."},{"time":37820,"text":"And a couple of things struck me about this."},{"time":40275,"text":"One, don't listen to career advisers."},{"time":44005,"text":"And two, actually this is a fascinating paradox for architecture,"},{"time":48661,"text":"which is that, as a society, we've never needed design thinking more,"},{"time":52931,"text":"and yet architecture was literally becoming unemployed."},{"time":56889,"text":"It strikes me that we talk very deeply about design,"},{"time":60440,"text":"but actually there's an economics behind architecture"},{"time":62556,"text":"that we don't talk about, and I think we need to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":65024,"text":"And a good place to start is your own paycheck."},{"time":68655,"text":"So, as a bottom-of-the-rung architecture graduate,"},{"time":71097,"text":"I might expect to earn about 24,000 pounds."},{"time":74073,"text":"That's about 36,000, 37,000 dollars."},{"time":77689,"text":"Now in terms of the whole world's population,"},{"time":79394,"text":"that already puts me in the top 1.95 richest people,"},{"time":84276,"text":"which raises the question of, who is it I'm working for?"},{"time":88036,"text":"The uncomfortable fact is that"},{"time":90747,"text":"actually almost everything that we call architecture today"},{"time":93631,"text":"is actually the business of designing"},{"time":95923,"text":"for about the richest one percent of the world's population,"},{"time":98848,"text":"and it always has been."},{"time":101077,"text":"The reason why we forgot that"},{"time":102824,"text":"is because the times in history when architecture"},{"time":104927,"text":"did the most to transform society were those times"},{"time":107852,"text":"when, actually, the one percent would build"},{"time":110509,"text":"on behalf of the 99 percent, for various different reasons,"},{"time":113544,"text":"whether that was through philanthropy in the 19th century,"},{"time":116159,"text":"communism in the early 20th,"},{"time":118429,"text":"the welfare state, and most recently, of course,"},{"time":121467,"text":"through this inflated real estate bubble."},{"time":125083,"text":"And all of those booms, in their own various ways,"},{"time":128391,"text":"have now kicked the bucket,"},{"time":130310,"text":"and we're back in this situation"},{"time":132596,"text":"where the smartest designers and architects in the world"},{"time":137512,"text":"are only really able to work for one percent of the population."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141292,"text":"Now it's not just that that's bad for democracy,"},{"time":143402,"text":"though I think it probably is,"},{"time":145241,"text":"it's actually not a very clever business strategy, actually."},{"time":148337,"text":"I think the challenge facing the next generation of architects"},{"time":151196,"text":"is, how are we going to turn our client"},{"time":153238,"text":"from the one percent to the 100 percent?"},{"time":156859,"text":"And I want to offer three slightly counterintuitive ideas"},{"time":160433,"text":"for how it might be done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162275,"text":"The first is, I think we need to question this idea"},{"time":165657,"text":"that architecture is about making buildings."},{"time":167948,"text":"Actually, a building is about the most expensive solution"},{"time":170692,"text":"you can think of to almost any given problem."},{"time":173708,"text":"And fundamentally, design should be much, much more interested"},{"time":176236,"text":"in solving problems and creating new conditions."},{"time":178968,"text":"So here's a story."},{"time":180490,"text":"The office was working with a school,"},{"time":182088,"text":"and they had an old Victorian school building."}]},{"cues":[{"time":184514,"text":"And they said to the architects, \"Look,"},{"time":187245,"text":"our corridors are an absolute nightmare."},{"time":189198,"text":"They're far too small. They get congested between classes."},{"time":191564,"text":"There's bullying. We can't control them."},{"time":193947,"text":"So what we want you to do is re-plan our entire building,"},{"time":196789,"text":"and we know it's going to cost several million pounds,"},{"time":198979,"text":"but we're reconciled to the fact.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":200890,"text":"And the team thought about this, and they went away,"},{"time":203596,"text":"and they said, \"Actually, don't do that."},{"time":205613,"text":"Instead, get rid of the school bell."},{"time":208393,"text":"And instead of having one school bell that goes off once,"},{"time":211222,"text":"have several smaller school bells that go off"},{"time":213480,"text":"in different places and different times,"},{"time":215728,"text":"distribute the traffic through the corridors.\""},{"time":217976,"text":"It solves the same problem,"},{"time":219393,"text":"but instead of spending several million pounds,"},{"time":222201,"text":"you spend several hundred pounds."},{"time":224344,"text":"Now, it looks like you're doing yourself out of a job,"},{"time":227144,"text":"but you're not. You're actually making yourself more useful."},{"time":229705,"text":"Architects are actually really, really good"},{"time":231178,"text":"at this kind of resourceful, strategic thinking."},{"time":233520,"text":"And the problem is that, like a lot of design professions,"},{"time":235482,"text":"we got fixated on the idea of providing"},{"time":237665,"text":"a particular kind of consumer product,"},{"time":239946,"text":"and I don't think that needs to be the case anymore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":242416,"text":"The second idea worth questioning is this 20th-century thing"},{"time":246617,"text":"that mass architecture is about big --"},{"time":249878,"text":"big buildings and big finance."},{"time":252472,"text":"Actually, we've got ourselves locked into this"},{"time":254561,"text":"Industrial Era mindset which says that"},{"time":256968,"text":"the only people who can make cities are large organizations"},{"time":260454,"text":"or corporations who build on our behalf,"},{"time":262972,"text":"procuring whole neighborhoods"},{"time":264780,"text":"in single, monolithic projects, and of course,"},{"time":268213,"text":"form follows finance."},{"time":270432,"text":"So what you end up with are single, monolithic neighborhoods"},{"time":273456,"text":"based on this kind of one-size-fits-all model."},{"time":277144,"text":"And a lot of people can't even afford them."},{"time":279657,"text":"But what if, actually, it's possible now for cities"},{"time":282624,"text":"to be made not just by the few with a lot"},{"time":285394,"text":"but also by the many with a bit?"},{"time":288582,"text":"And when they do, they bring with them"},{"time":289876,"text":"a completely different set of values about the place that they want to live."},{"time":293215,"text":"And it raises really interesting questions about,"},{"time":295319,"text":"how will we plan cities? How will finance development?"},{"time":298602,"text":"How will we sell design services?"},{"time":300263,"text":"What would it mean for democratic societies"},{"time":302503,"text":"to offer their citizens a right to build?"},{"time":304903,"text":"And in a way it should be kind of obvious, right,"},{"time":307183,"text":"that in the 21st century, maybe cities can be developed by citizens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312652,"text":"And thirdly, we need to remember that,"},{"time":315816,"text":"from a strictly economic point of view,"},{"time":318167,"text":"design shares a category with sex and care of the elderly --"},{"time":323013,"text":"mostly it's done by amateurs."},{"time":325609,"text":"And that's a good thing."},{"time":327495,"text":"Most of the work takes place outside of the monetary economy"},{"time":330965,"text":"in what's called the social economy or the core economy,"},{"time":333025,"text":"which is people doing it for themselves."},{"time":335417,"text":"And the problem is that, up until now,"},{"time":338665,"text":"it was the monetary economy which had"},{"time":340467,"text":"all the infrastructure and all the tools."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342625,"text":"So the challenge we face is, how are we going"},{"time":344448,"text":"to build the tools, the infrastructure and the institutions"},{"time":347682,"text":"for architecture's social economy?"},{"time":349422,"text":"And that began with open-source software."},{"time":352154,"text":"And over the last few years, it's been moving"},{"time":354522,"text":"into the physical world with open-source hardware,"},{"time":357017,"text":"which are freely shared blueprints"},{"time":358547,"text":"that anyone can download and make for themselves."},{"time":362593,"text":"And that's where 3D printing gets really, really interesting."},{"time":365834,"text":"Right? When suddenly you had a 3D printer"},{"time":369370,"text":"that was open-source, the parts for which"},{"time":370924,"text":"could be made on another 3D printer."},{"time":373205,"text":"Or the same idea here, which is for a CNC machine,"},{"time":376266,"text":"which is like a large printer that can cut sheets of plywood."},{"time":380762,"text":"What these technologies are doing is radically"},{"time":383576,"text":"lowering the thresholds of time and cost and skill."},{"time":386657,"text":"They're challenging the idea that"},{"time":388239,"text":"if you want something to be affordable it's got to be one-size-fits-all."},{"time":392065,"text":"And they're distributing massively"},{"time":394398,"text":"really complex manufacturing capabilities."},{"time":397285,"text":"We're moving into this future where the factory is everywhere,"},{"time":401416,"text":"and increasingly that means"},{"time":402611,"text":"that the design team is everyone."},{"time":405898,"text":"That really is an industrial revolution."},{"time":408424,"text":"And when we think that the major ideological conflicts"},{"time":411640,"text":"that we inherited were all based around this question"},{"time":413658,"text":"of who should control the means of production,"},{"time":415570,"text":"and these technologies are coming back with a solution:"},{"time":418297,"text":"actually, maybe no one. All of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":422286,"text":"And we were fascinated by"},{"time":424455,"text":"what that might mean for architecture."},{"time":427062,"text":"So about a year and a half ago,"},{"time":429584,"text":"we started working on a project called WikiHouse,"},{"time":431480,"text":"and WikiHouse is an open-source construction system."},{"time":434754,"text":"And the idea is to make it possible for anyone"},{"time":437552,"text":"to go online, access a freely shared library"},{"time":439936,"text":"of 3D models which they can download and adapt in,"},{"time":444397,"text":"at the moment, SketchUp, because it's free, and it's easy to use,"},{"time":447788,"text":"and almost at the click of a switch"},{"time":450347,"text":"they can generate a set of cutting files"},{"time":452831,"text":"which allow them, in effect,"},{"time":454872,"text":"to print out the parts from a house using a CNC machine"},{"time":458060,"text":"and a standard sheet material like plywood."},{"time":461271,"text":"And the parts are all numbered,"},{"time":464391,"text":"and basically what you end up with is a really big IKEA kit."},{"time":468568,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":470839,"text":"And it goes together without any bolts."},{"time":473105,"text":"It uses wedge and peg connections."},{"time":475295,"text":"And even the mallets to make it"},{"time":477439,"text":"can be provided on the cutting sheets as well."},{"time":479919,"text":"And a team of about two or three people,"},{"time":482456,"text":"working together, can build this."},{"time":484495,"text":"They don't need any traditional construction skills."},{"time":486975,"text":"They don't need a huge array of power tools or anything like that,"},{"time":490126,"text":"and they can build a small house of about this size"},{"time":492639,"text":"in about a day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":497403,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":504706,"text":"And what you end up with is just the basic chassis of a house"},{"time":507701,"text":"onto which you can then apply systems like windows"},{"time":510160,"text":"and cladding and insulation and services"},{"time":512218,"text":"based on what's cheap and what's available."},{"time":515267,"text":"Of course, the house is never finished."},{"time":517452,"text":"We're shifting our heads here, so the house is not a finished product."},{"time":520333,"text":"With the CNC machine, you can make new parts for it"},{"time":523090,"text":"over its life or even use it to make the house next door."},{"time":526947,"text":"So we can begin to see the seed of a completely open-source,"},{"time":530385,"text":"citizen-led urban development model, potentially."}]},{"cues":[{"time":534660,"text":"And we and others have built a few prototypes around the world now,"},{"time":538210,"text":"and some really interesting lessons here."},{"time":540331,"text":"One of them is that it's always incredibly sociable."},{"time":542658,"text":"People get confused between construction work and having fun."},{"time":547356,"text":"But the principles of openness go right down"},{"time":550015,"text":"into the really mundane, physical details."},{"time":552821,"text":"Like, never designing a piece that can't be lifted up."},{"time":555824,"text":"Or, when you're designing a piece,"},{"time":557123,"text":"make sure you either can't put it in the wrong way round,"},{"time":560003,"text":"or, if you do, it doesn't matter, because it's symmetrical."},{"time":562956,"text":"Probably the principal which runs deepest with us"},{"time":566998,"text":"is the principal set out by Linus Torvalds,"},{"time":569953,"text":"the open-source pioneer,"},{"time":572678,"text":"which was that idea of, \"Be lazy like a fox.\""},{"time":575967,"text":"Don't reinvent the wheel every time."},{"time":577676,"text":"Take what already works, and adapt it for your own needs."},{"time":581469,"text":"Contrary to almost everything that you might get taught"},{"time":584052,"text":"at an architecture school, copying is good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588149,"text":"Which is appropriate, because actually,"},{"time":590150,"text":"this approach is not innovative."},{"time":591930,"text":"It's actually how we built buildings"},{"time":593539,"text":"for hundreds of years before the Industrial Revolution"},{"time":596035,"text":"in these sorts of community barn-raisings."},{"time":598462,"text":"The only difference between traditional"},{"time":600606,"text":"vernacular architecture and open-source architecture"},{"time":603014,"text":"might be a web connection,"},{"time":605134,"text":"but it's a really, really big difference."},{"time":607946,"text":"We shared the whole of WikiHouse"},{"time":609377,"text":"under a Creative Commons license,"},{"time":611219,"text":"and now what's just beginning to happen"},{"time":612641,"text":"is that groups around the world are beginning to take it"},{"time":614623,"text":"and use it and hack it and tinker with it, and it's amazing."},{"time":617362,"text":"There's a cool group over in Christchurch in New Zealand"},{"time":620327,"text":"looking at post-earthquake development housing,"},{"time":623462,"text":"and thanks to the TED city Prize,"},{"time":626710,"text":"we're working with an awesome group in one of Rio's favelas"},{"time":629449,"text":"to set up a kind of community factory"},{"time":631938,"text":"and micro-university."},{"time":633852,"text":"These are very, very small beginnings,"},{"time":635716,"text":"and actually there's more people in the last week"},{"time":638591,"text":"who have got in touch and they're not even on this map."},{"time":640774,"text":"I hope next time you see it, you won't even be able to see the map."}]},{"cues":[{"time":644514,"text":"We're aware that WikiHouse is a very, very small answer,"},{"time":648963,"text":"but it's a small answer to a really, really big question,"},{"time":652535,"text":"which is that globally, right now, the fastest-growing cities"},{"time":656311,"text":"are not skyscraper cities."},{"time":658542,"text":"They're self-made cities in one form or another."},{"time":662638,"text":"If we're talking about the 21st-century city,"},{"time":666262,"text":"these are the guys who are going to be making it."},{"time":668886,"text":"You know, like it or not, welcome to the world's biggest design team."}]},{"cues":[{"time":673368,"text":"So if we're serious about problems"},{"time":675494,"text":"like climate change, urbanization and health,"},{"time":679648,"text":"actually, our existing development models aren't going to do it."},{"time":683546,"text":"As I think Robert Neuwirth said, there isn't a bank"},{"time":685634,"text":"or a corporation or a government or an NGO"},{"time":688411,"text":"who's going to be able to do it"},{"time":689797,"text":"if we treat citizens only as consumers."},{"time":693446,"text":"How extraordinary would it be, though, if collectively"},{"time":697227,"text":"we were to develop solutions not just to the problem"},{"time":699500,"text":"of structure that we've been working on,"},{"time":701914,"text":"but to infrastructure problems like solar-powered air conditioning,"},{"time":706634,"text":"off-grid energy, off-grid sanitation --"},{"time":709450,"text":"low-cost, open-source, high-performance solutions"},{"time":713379,"text":"that anyone can very, very easily make,"},{"time":715319,"text":"and to put them all into a commons"},{"time":717220,"text":"where they're owned by everyone and they're accessible by everyone?"},{"time":721568,"text":"A kind of Wikipedia for stuff?"},{"time":725738,"text":"And once something's in the commons,"},{"time":727779,"text":"it will always be there."},{"time":729135,"text":"How much would that change the rules?"},{"time":732663,"text":"And I think the technology's on our side."}]},{"cues":[{"time":736099,"text":"If design's great project in the 20th century"},{"time":739759,"text":"was the democratization of consumption --"},{"time":743520,"text":"that was Henry Ford, Levittown, Coca-Cola, IKEA —"},{"time":749946,"text":"I think design's great project in the 21st century"},{"time":753568,"text":"is the democratization of production."},{"time":756440,"text":"And when it comes to architecture in cities,"},{"time":759120,"text":"that really matters."},{"time":761192,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":762946,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}